article.headline: Morgan St. 64, Delaware St. 50
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Reggie Holmes scored 15 points and Morgan State defeated Delaware State 64-50 on Saturday. Holmes was one of three Bears (19-11, 12-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) to score in double figures. Jermaine Bolden added 12 points and Marquise Kately chipped in with 10. After leading 36-28 at halftime, Morgan State opened the second half with a 14-4 run, resulting in a 50-32 lead on a Kevin Thompson layup with 14:24 remaining. The Bears scored 11 points off of 11 Delaware State (7-23, 5-10) turnovers. The Hornets, who shot 38.5 percent form the floor (20 of 52) were led by Fred Bouie with 16 points. Morgan State outrebounded the Hornets 37-29. Thompson led the Bears with eight rebounds. The Hornets lost their fourth straight game.
